INSTALLATION GUIDE:

1. install nodejs, express and mongodb on your system then run the commands
2.  npm install
3. go in the expresshogan directory
4.  npm start
5. open your browser and type the url :  "http://localhost:3000"



How to install node js in ubuntu:
Run the following commands one by one

    sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
    sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install nodejs
    
    
To install express run the following commands:

    npm install -g express
    

To install mongodb:

    sudo apt-get install mongodb-org




